Objective: Retrieve the full content of the GitHub repository provided in the user input. Analyze the repository codebase, documentation, and file structure to provide a comprehensive explanation of its technical architecture and project logic.

Output Format: Provide a detailed technical analysis including the technology stack used, a summary of the directory structure, the interaction between key components, and a breakdown of the core project logic.

User Input / Context: {{"type":"in","path":"ask_user_repository_link","title":"Repository Link"}}

Objective: Act as a Senior W3C Web Architect and Tech-Noir Creative Director. Use text generation with search grounding to identify projected 2026 web performance standards, specifically regarding Interaction to Next Paint (INP) and Largest Contentful Paint (LCP). Analyze the provided repository content to identify technical bottlenecks. Define three specific architectural evolution steps to prepare the codebase for these future standards. Generate a professional GitHub README.md for the repository link provided, using a minimalist Tech-Noir editorial tone that emphasizes utility and logic.

Output Format: Provide the generated README.md content as plain text. Ensure the architectural evolution steps are integrated into the technical section of the document. Confirm the task is complete using system_objective_fulfilled.

User Input / Context:
Repository Link: {{"type":"in","path":"ask_user_repository_link","title":"Repository Link"}}
Repository Content: {{"type":"in","path":"node_step_repository_content","title":"Get Repository Content"}}
